# Four Ways of Linking Files in HTML

## 1. Linking External CSS File

Use the `<link>` tag in the `<head>` to link an external CSS file.

```html
<head>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
```

---

## 2. Linking External JavaScript File

Use the `<script>` tag, typically before the closing `</body>` tag.

```html
<body>
  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
```

---

## 3. Internal CSS

Use the `<style>` tag within the `<head>` section to write CSS directly inside the HTML file.

```html
<head>
  <style>
    body {
      background-color: lightblue;
    }
  </style>
</head>
```

---

## 4. Internal JavaScript

Use the `<script>` tag directly in the HTML file to include JavaScript code.

```html
<body>
  <script>
    alert("Welcome to the site!");
  </script>
</body>
```
